reviews.text: There is so much to see in this beautiful house! Everything is authentic to the way it was originally and the house is really in great condition. I loved walking around inside. Will have to come back during the summer to see more of the grounds!

I love this place! If you like history, architecture and design; this is the place to be! I have gone on countless tours and I have to say my favorite is during Christmas time! It must be a favorite because tours are very scare during that time. Make sure to purchase tickets beforehand guaranteeing your tour! Great customer service, you won’t be disappointed!

I thought it was pretty fun going here. And it was really cool how the mansion looked and the outside of it. Starting on the outside, there were these little trails going around in the woods around the area. (I was there in the fall/beginning of winter so the trails were closed so I don't know exactly how far they go) There are also paths going through the trees and down to the shore from the mansion. Then down at the shore you can walk out on this little boardwalk thing and you can see the lift bridge in the distance from there which is pretty cool. Then on the inside it is so historic looking. There are a bunch of old furniture and original rooms. People might think it is scary there because of the murders but it really isn't. I just thought it looked really cool. I recommend going here if you have some spare time around the Duluth area.

Very disappointed to find that management has changed the Classic tours to self-guided. I missed the experience of having a knowledgeable guide, and having them only for the more expensive tours is elitist and exclusionary. Know for a fact this decision was made in an attempt to cut corners and reduce staffing costs, get Glensheen continues to pay for advertisements seeking out new employees. 0/10 recommend unless you can afford the outrageous specialty tours. Tip your tour guide!

Place is so amazing, so surreal here. I would recommend coming to see it for your self and explore Duluth upfront and personal. The mansion is such a glimpse into how things use to be. I'm blown away and definitely coming back. Picture of lake superior from the mansion shoreline , just beautiful.

Super fun place for kids. The train museum is so much fun and you don't have to even be a huge train fan. They have a working model railroad in the middle of the building, several trains that you can climb in and on. They have an outdoor section where you can climb up a large crane and look around. Gift shop, ice cream shop (closed in winter), and then store fronts from the time period. Very cool place to spend a dreary afternoon.

We have always had a good experience when coming. We have been on several different train rides now and continue to come back. I have always thought the tickets are reasonable and you get to walk around the depot when you arrive. Have have spent at least 2 hours of looking and each time we go we still roam around the depot. The have a vending area along with bathrooms next to it and also in the entry. A very nice gift shop with lots to choose from. Everyone is very friendly and helpful. We will be coming back again.

Coming here was such am awesome experience, and is definitely the most interesting museum I have ever been to.

There are "four floors of fun", with the train stuff at the bottom. There are real artifacts here and rare and well maintained trains. What impressed me the most was the log crane and the train snow plows.

If you are in Duluth, have never been here before and have a few hours to spare, I would HIGHLY recommend coming here. I am not even a huge train nerd and I thoroughly enjoyed it.
You will get your money's worth here. The railroad museum is so awesome and full of history. They even have two more museums upstairs that are just as interesting!.

Outstanding Musum,
Parking is Not Free on any Downtown Street.
Unless, you’re visiting Duluth for a few days.
In the summer, it’s a perfect walk. 

As fair as the Administration Price. It’s not over price. It cost money to keep this building open. Lights, Water Insurance & a few people are on the pay roll. Provided by the generous Membership  oh, almost all of the Museums is close on Mondays. Probably for exterior cleaning day.

We did like the mechanism of  aerial lift bridge. It’s similar to that you saw in clear water. This one covers the entire entrance to the lake, however the clear water one is partially covering the entry to lake and rest is all bridge. Wait for sometime and notice how it gets open as there would be couple of time ships crossing over

I mean, if you're in Duluth you have to check it out! Very pretty during special events (4th of July, and when lit up at night). Seeing the big salties come in and out under the bridge, and through such a narrow channel is pretty cool.
An icon for Duluth, and gateway to Lake Superior. Also cool area to walk around and watch huge boats come and go. Nice little park near by as well
This is a very nice place to walk around and watch ships enter the harbor. I highly recommend seeing this place if you're staying in duluth or just passing through.
Iconic part of Duluth.  I enjoyed seeing it on a cold Tuesday night, but the chance of it rising to let a ship go through was slim to none.

I really enjoyed this zoo. Its not the biggest but it does have a variety of different animals. You could definitely spend a few hours here looking at the animals and walking around outside. Very beautiful area. The staff are also very friendly and knowledgeable.
Awesome Zoo!  Great Staff and Lots to See!  I hope to go there during the summer sometime to see all their other exhibits that were put away for the fall/winter.

I love zoos, and I really want to love this one in my hometown, but it is honestly mediocre at best.  The animals that they do have are great!  My kids love the barnyard petting zoo, and the train. Many of the outside enclosures are empty.  My 3 year old kept asking "what's in there?", when I responded several times that there were no animals in there, she asked "why are all these empty?  Where are all the animals?". With that being said, we will continue to support our local zoo.  It has a lot of potential.

Have always enjoyed coming here. The tiger and the lions are worth seeing alone. Price of admission is a small price to pay to come to this zoo and have a great time. 

The zoo itself sits in a beautiful valley, a river and falls runs right through the middle of it. It is packed to the gills with big and small animals. Well worth a stop.

I absolutely love this place ... every time I come to Duluth I come here at least twice a year. It is a non-profit organization and people here  truly love their animals. You can see it by how they interact

I did enjoy the restaurant it was a valentine treat from my friend Melissa. Anne was our server and sat at the bar. Although she was a bit stiff she was fun. Melissa tends to point out the unusual like the bottle sweaters. So our server was quick to say oops you know she really needed to realize that the customer had and has the Oddball sense of humor. Now this talk about food. I got brought to this restaurant because Melissa was having a spaghetti craving. This is a serious thing for her. Our server figured out how to get her the spaghetti she wanted when it was not even on the menu. I had these shrimp alfredo fettuccine and my review of it is top top marks! The only problem I had with the entire experience was the pricing. And I lit the pricing go because it says chef. Anytime you see the word chef you are going to pay bigger money for Stuff. And although I enjoyed the fettuccine I don't know that it was worth 30 some dollars but it was good and Anne was nice enough to get me extra shrimp. It's a good little restaurant and I mean little. Or intimate might be better. Go to Duluth and just before you get to Grandma's look to your right sitting right on the corner at the light.

If I could rate 0 stars I would. This restaurant ruined my Valentines Day.

My partner and I ordered two tasting flights, after two flights he found one glass of wine he’d like to try, which I didn’t like particularly. I had a bit.

When we ordered dessert, I was refused a glass of port, despite only having a total of two glasses at most by that point.

I had booked a room to stay, intending to see music after our meal. Instead  lead I just drove an hour and a half home immediately, crying most of the way. 

I feel discriminated and completely disappointed, and will not be returning. 

The food was fine but not worth the serving. I’ve found Va Benne to be similar quality, cheaper, and I’ve never had any disappointments like this.
Good food. A tad spendy but if you want a quiet higher class dining feel it delivers
Very good Fettuccine Alfredo. It reminds me of my travels back in Italy! I'm very pleased. Pasta was perfectly done and the sauce was nice and sharp  Just like it's supposed to be

This place is awesome for wine lovers. They have dozens of wine flight options available at a very reasonable price giving you the chance to try new wines. The service is superb but the food isn't great. The pasta is over cooked and the fries were soggy. However, since my husband is Italian we are harder to please when eating Italian food. Overall this place is a good choice when visiting Duluth.

This is a wonderful upscale restaurant in Canal Park. We chose to eat there because the menu has different food options than what's found at most other restaurants and it was a great choice! The food and drinks were delicious! One of the best meals I've ever had. The menu is also very vegetarian, vegan, and gluten free friendly. Plus the majority of their food and drinks are locally sourced (they even list the local businesses in a booklet on your table). It's a unique dining experience that I'd definitely recommend the next time you're in Duluth!

Food is fabulous, service is top notch. It's unique and different and I like that. I could live on that soup forever! I like that we know every farm everything comes from and its locally sourced. Two thumbs up👍👍
Great food. The bar is a surprisingly cool place to have a drink. I've always had great service. Thanks guys and girls!
Delicious, fresh, and local food. Vegan and vegetarian option available. Nice calm and quiet spot for a relaxing dinner.
Good and knowledgeable servers, fine wine selection, great and unique menu. You pay for what you get and it is well worth it. Half price wine on Wednesday nights.

I love this place with all my heart and soul. The food is always amazing as well as the employees. There is only one problem and it is that my order is always wrong. Call or order in person I am always missing something/given one order wrong, given less of what I've ordered, or getting extremely spicy food when I asked for it not to be spicy. I've spent close to or over $1,000 here and I've given up on believing my order is correct, but the food is too good not to come back. If I have to check my food visually and taste test it every time I'll gladly do it, I just wish I didn't have to.

The food and staff are great and friendly. Whenever I come here with my partner we tend to get a party platter, you get a little bit of a lot of things and it always fills us up. It's great if you are looking for a variety of items but don't want to order too much.

We were invited by our friend to have dinner. Food was horrible. Waiters they don't know what they were serving. They need more crew. They even missed the order. we ordered lamb curry, Thali, chicken tikka masala.
I will not recommend ruin our trip all the way from Santa Rosa.

this is my current favourite Indian restaurant. the dinner menu has a good selection, and the food is great. they also have a wider array of naan-like options than any other place i have tried. the parking lot is cramped and can be difficult to navigate.
The food is fresh and plentiful. The restaurant is easy to get to. The food is good.

This is a really awesome place.  This is the second time I have been here, and I would definitely return here for another round.  I travel for a living, but work for a trucking company local to Duluth.  Awesome food, friendly Atmosphere.  Thank you folks for a place with such a family friendly atmosphere

My son had asked to eat at a Mexican restaurant in Duluth. I had always passed Maya and thought it would be worth a try. I was completely wrong. When my son and I entered the restaurant there was only a couple standing at the register waiting to pay. Finally a woman came to the register and took their money. She didn't acknowledge us and immediately walked away. We sat on the chairs next to the please wait to be seated sign. There didn't seem to be many people in the restaurant but then another party entered and joined us in our wait. After a while longer with no one to greet or seat us or explain the wait we left and went to Mexico Lindo where we were immediate seated and the food and service was great. I'm assuming the food at Maya must be good or they wouldn't exist but it was the worst service I've ever had.

Summary: NEVER COME HERE!
 
A friend and I went to Maya’s Mexican Restaurant in Duluth MN. Upon arrive the service had already proven itself terrible, as there was quite a wait just to be seated, even though it was empty. At first my friend asked to be seated in one side of the restaurant, which more dimly lit but was promptly told there was no open seats there. When we asked for a booth, we were given a table that was half booth, half flimsy chairs that were somewhat falling apart. We asked for another table, but we were told that the other booths were dirty, and we would have to wait a bit to have them washed. Not wanting to spend more time waiting we sat down and waited another ten to fifteen minutes for our menu’s and chip basket. My order and service were somewhat satisfactory from then on, but my friend’s service got worse. She decided against her first choice after the waitress mentioned that it was served with a few things she didn’t like. After looking over the menu she decided on the chicken burrito for $12.99, as it stated it came with cheese, lettuce and other toppings. When she ordered the burrito, the waitress said she would have to pay extra for anything the menu said it have. Though the worst events happened after she got her food, as her burrito was only shredded chicken wrapped in a shell with a small bit a cheese she had to pay extra for. After eating for a few minutes, she suddenly started gagging and pulled out a small hair from her mouth. When we told the waitress about it, she said we need to show her the hair for her to say anything to the cook. When my friend said she won’t pay for the waitress to best put it got an attitude and told my friend she was being rude all day. She ended having to pay for her meal, hair and all.

First time I've ever ate here, and I wasn't disappointed! Good choice of dishes, there were three of us and the bill wasn't to bad. We got a huge portions! I have enough leftovers to make Mexican omelets in the morning!
Love their chips and salsa.  Good lunch menu selection with a nice authentic feel.   Outside seating is available weather dependent.

So I had my order delivered to West Duluth. My delivery driver was very prompt, even though he forgot my soda at the store, he went and grabbed some at the nearest convenient store. Now that is service! I have never had a bad experience with Pizza Luce, but this last experience will definitely make me order more often from them! Kudos to their delivery drivers.

We ordered in, it got to us in the time they said it would , but our pizza seemed old , half cold and taste wasn't even close to amazing. same with our cheesy bread, not impressed.. the only thing we ate the most of was the wings. For how expensive it was I thought it was going to be amazing, it was not. I definitely will not eat here again. Again, I am not impressed with the experience 🤦

I was in town for a work meeting and the whole team went here for lunch. For a large group and a busy lunch schedule they still got our food to us quickly. The food was worth the visit and the ambiance was awesome.

One of my favorite restaurants in Duluth. We could not decide on which pizza to order so the server suggested that we get 2 different kinds on 1 pizza. It was perfect for us and the food was delicious as usual.
So many great vegetarian, vegan, dairy and gluten free options! Gluten free stuffed shells were amazing. Molly bar was very good. Great and quick service and very reasonable prices.
Nice menu.  Enjoyed the burger and fish fry.  Our server was very busy but still provided us with  great service.  We recommend.
Best fries in town. As two meat lovers we LOVE the wild rice burger here too! Great beer selection and huge menu that covers any food needs.

Very good food and beer here! Super friendly and fast service! I couldn’t believe how fast the food came out. They have the best poutine I have ever had. The overall atmosphere added to the great dining experience. You must go here if you are in Duluth!
Second visit to Fitger’s, still excellent. The wild rice burger was delicious and the fish tacos are always great! Nice ambiance... feels like a college pub.

Have been going to Fitgers for years, before I could even pronounce the name correctly. They have solid food options there, with their main focus being burgers, and not a tone of variety, but they so a good job on what they do make. They also have a great variety in beers, mostly self brewed right there and are quite delicious. Definitely worth a try if never been!

Yes, all the yeses! This place was unassuming when I walked in but blew me away after that. From seating to end of the meal everything was perfect. The menu is unconventional as it comes but full of character and Duluth charm. I will definitely be back, well done, well done!

Go here! The best breakfast!!
Coffee is great, eggs, pancakes, everything. You can’t go wrong. Fresh and flavorful. Fast service even with a large party. When you’re finished with your meal check out their garden. So lovely!!

This is by far one of my most favorite places to eat! The atmosphere is wonderful and the service was great. I myself am a vegetarian and they have plenty of vegetarian and vegan dishes to choose from. I also love that they support local produce and are mostly organic! The food always tastes great, portions are perfect, and presentation is beautiful! Highly recommend!

Wow! The food and atmosphere are fabulous. We were told by friends to check out this spot and we were not disappointed. Food was fresh, local, organic, abd delicious. The menu has a lot of unique and known options. It was actually difficult to decide what to have as there were so many things I wanted to try. The staff was very friendly and helpful. We will definitely be keeping this spot on our list of places to go to when in Duluth!

If you want to eat the same stuff that all of the chain restaurants are serving then don't go here, if on the other hand you want food that tastes great,  served by staff that is genuinely happy to see you and you want to support the local economy because they buy as much as possible from local sources. Then you definitely want to go here, normally when we get up to Duluth at least one of our meals is at the Duluth Grill.  They've earned our loyalty with great food, great service and great prices.
Nice menu.  Enjoyed the burger and fish fry.  Our server was very busy but still provided us with  great service.  We recommend.
Best fries in town. As two meat lovers we LOVE the wild rice burger here too! Great beer selection and huge menu that covers any food needs.

Very good food and beer here! Super friendly and fast service! I couldn’t believe how fast the food came out. They have the best poutine I have ever had. The overall atmosphere added to the great dining experience. You must go here if you are in Duluth!
Second visit to Fitger’s, still excellent. The wild rice burger was delicious and the fish tacos are always great! Nice ambiance... feels like a college pub.

They have solid food options there, with their main focus being burgers, and not a tone of variety, but they so a good job on what they do make. They also have a great variety in beers, mostly self brewed right there and are quite delicious. Definitely worth a try if never been!
